item.title: Deleting objects on different heights
item.dc:creator: @Tatemo Tatemo
item.description:
@Tatemo wrote:

I myself have tried this before. If you delete an object at the coords and you load into height level one. It deletes all the objects on height level one at the coords specified but not at height level 0. IF you delete an object and load at height level 0 it deletes all the ones at height level 0 u specified but none on height level 1 so yeah I dunno

item.title: Deleting objects on different heights
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

This is server side, 90% sure.

If you search: deletethatobj in client.java, it should show a list of objects previously deleted, basically, just enter the X and Y co ordinates of the objects, and they should be removed.
